body:
Hi @shu-yusa:

There was an issue with a javascript library pulled into MLflow which caused this issue. This should not affect `0.9.0` and was fixed in #1007 in `master` branch. My recommendation is to either use `branch-0.9` or rebase `master` to post #1007 fix.
@mparkhe Understood. Thank you for the quick response!

You may need to re-build javascript server code, after rebasing.
https://github.com/mlflow/mlflow/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.rst#install-node-modules
@mparkhe got it. I will try that. Thanks again.
Rebuilding the package isn't a very satisfactory resolution to this issue -- Y'all should release a fix, instead.
I installed mlflow 0.9.0 from pypi -- time for 0.9.1 ??
I installed from branch branch-0.9 -- still can't type

Yes, @mparkhe  installing from pypi mlflow==0.9.0 you can't type -- I've also tried installing from source, branch-0.9 and master, and rebuilding the js dependencies as mentioned in #1113 and still can't input in the web form.

@timothyjlaurent @shu-yusa thanks for catching & reporting this issue! It is a legitimate bug & we've fixed it in MLflow 0.9.0.1 (a PyPI-only release). You can upgrade to the new version via pip install --upgrade mlflow - let me know if there are any other issues, and thanks again + apologies for the inconvenience!
Woot!! Thanks @smurching... Maybe a good one to add to the release checklist.
